function Zf(e) {

        a += e;

                a += r)

                a += r);

const $j = ["top", "right", "bottom", "left"]
  , ir = Math.min
  , ht = Math.max
  , po = Math.round
  , yn = Math.floor
  , ti = e => ({
    x: e,
    y: e
})
  , qj = {
    left: "right",
    right: "left",
    bottom: "top",
    top: "bottom"
}
  , Qj = {
    start: "end",
    end: "start"
};
function Dc(e, t, r) {
    return ht(e, ir(t, r))
}
function wi(e, t) {
    return typeof e == "function" ? e(t) : e
}
function ji(e) {
    return e.split("-")[0]
}
function La(e) {
    return e.split("-")[1]
}
function Jd(e) {
    return e === "x" ? "y" : "x"
}
function Zd(e) {
    return e === "y" ? "height" : "width"
}
function rr(e) {
    return ["top", "bottom"].includes(ji(e)) ? "y" : "x"
}
function eu(e) {
    return Jd(rr(e))
}
function Kj(e, t, r) {
    r === void 0 && (r = !1);
    const a = La(e)
      , s = eu(e)
      , n = Zd(s);
    let o = s === "x" ? a === (r ? "end" : "start") ? "right" : "left" : a === "start" ? "bottom" : "top";
    return t.reference[n] > t.floating[n] && (o = mo(o)),
    [o, mo(o)]
}
function Xj(e) {
    const t = mo(e);
    return [Hc(e), t, Hc(t)]
}
function Hc(e) {
    return e.replace(/start|end/g, t => Qj[t])
}
function Jj(e, t, r) {
    const a = ["left", "right"]
      , s = ["right", "left"]
      , n = ["top", "bottom"]
      , o = ["bottom", "top"];
    switch (e) {
    case "top":
    case "bottom":
        return r ? t ? s : a : t ? a : s;
    case "left":
    case "right":
        return t ? n : o;
    default:
        return []
    }
}
function Zj(e, t, r, a) {
    const s = La(e);
    let n = Jj(ji(e), r === "start", a);
    return s && (n = n.map(o => o + "-" + s),
    t && (n = n.concat(n.map(Hc)))),
    n
}
function mo(e) {
    return e.replace(/left|right|bottom|top/g, t => qj[t])
}
function e1(e) {
    return {
        top: 0,
        right: 0,
        bottom: 0,
        left: 0,
        ...e
    }
}
function px(e) {
    return typeof e != "number" ? e1(e) : {
        top: e,
        right: e,
        bottom: e,
        left: e
    }
}
function ho(e) {
    const {x: t, y: r, width: a, height: s} = e;
    return {
        width: a,
        height: s,
        top: r,
        left: t,
        right: t + a,
        bottom: r + s,
        x: t,
        y: r
    }
}
function om(e, t, r) {
    let {reference: a, floating: s} = e;
    const n = rr(t)
      , o = eu(t)
      , l = Zd(o)
      , c = ji(t)
      , d = n === "y"
      , u = a.x + a.width / 2 - s.width / 2
      , p = a.y + a.height / 2 - s.height / 2
      , h = a[l] / 2 - s[l] / 2;
    let f;
    switch (c) {
    case "top":
        f = {
            x: u,
            y: a.y - s.height
        };
        break;
    case "bottom":
        f = {
            x: u,
            y: a.y + a.height
        };
        break;
    case "right":
        f = {
            x: a.x + a.width,
            y: p
        };
        break;
    case "left":
        f = {
            x: a.x - s.width,
            y: p
        };
        break;
    default:
        f = {
            x: a.x,
            y: a.y
        }
    }
    switch (La(t)) {
    case "start":

function uN(e, t) {
    const r = Math.abs(t.top - e.y)
      , a = Math.abs(t.bottom - e.y)
      , s = Math.abs(t.right - e.x)
      , n = Math.abs(t.left - e.x);
    switch (Math.min(r, a, s, n)) {
    case n:
        return "left";
    case s:
        return "right";
    case r:
        return "top";
    case a:
        return "bottom";
    default:
        throw new Error("unreachable")
    }
}
function pN(e, t, r=5) {
    const a = [];
    switch (t) {
    case "top":
        a.push({
            x: e.x - r,
            y: e.y + r
        }, {
            x: e.x + r,
            y: e.y + r
        });
        break;
    case "bottom":
        a.push({
            x: e.x - r,
            y: e.y - r
        }, {
            x: e.x + r,
            y: e.y - r
        });
        break;
    case "left":
        a.push({
            x: e.x + r,
            y: e.y - r
        }, {
            x: e.x + r,
            y: e.y + r
        });
        break;
    case "right":
        a.push({
            x: e.x - r,
            y: e.y - r
        }, {
            x: e.x - r,
            y: e.y + r
        });
        break
    }
    return a
}

function hN(e, t) {
    const {x: r, y: a} = e;
    let s = !1;
    for (let n = 0, o = t.length - 1; n < t.length; o = n++) {
        const l = t[n].x
          , c = t[n].y
          , d = t[o].x
          , u = t[o].y;
        c > a != u > a && r < (d - l) * (a - c) / (u - c) + l && (s = !s)
    }
    return s
}
function gN(e) {

    return t.sort( (r, a) => r.x < a.x ? -1 : r.x > a.x ? 1 : r.y < a.y ? -1 : r.y > a.y ? 1 : 0),
    fN(t)
}
function fN(e) {
    if (e.length <= 1)
        return e.slice();
    const t = [];
    for (let a = 0; a < e.length; a++) {
        const s = e[a];
        for (; t.length >= 2; ) {
            const n = t[t.length - 1]
              , o = t[t.length - 2];
            if ((n.x - o.x) * (s.y - o.y) >= (n.y - o.y) * (s.x - o.x))
                t.pop();
            else
                break
        }
        t.push(s)
    }
    t.pop();
    const r = [];
    for (let a = e.length - 1; a >= 0; a--) {
        const s = e[a];
        for (; r.length >= 2; ) {
            const n = r[r.length - 1]
              , o = r[r.length - 2];
            if ((n.x - o.x) * (s.y - o.y) >= (n.y - o.y) * (s.x - o.x))
                r.pop();
            else
                break
        }
        r.push(s)
    }
    return r.pop(),
    t.length === 1 && r.length === 1 && t[0].x === r[0].x && t[0].y === r[0].y ? t : t.concat(r)
}

function dt() {
    const {data: e, isLoading: t, error: r} = ae({
        queryKey: ["/api/auth/user"],
        retry: !1,
        refetchOnWindowFocus: !1,
        refetchOnMount: !0,
        refetchOnReconnect: !1,
        staleTime: 1 / 0,
        gcTime: 6e5,
        throwOnError: !1,
        queryFn: async () => {
            try {
                const s = await fetch("/api/auth/user", {
                    credentials: "include"
                });
                if (!s.ok) {
                    if (s.status === 401)
                        return null;
                    throw new Error(`Authentication check failed: ${s.status}`)
                }
                return await s.json()
            } catch {
                return null
            }
        }
    })
      , a = !!(e && e.id);
    return {
        user: e,
        isLoading: t,
        isAuthenticated: a,
        error: r
    }
}

function Gx() {
    return i.jsx("section", {
        className: "py-20 md:py-32 bg-white",
        children: i.jsx("div", {
            className: "container mx-auto px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-20 max-w-7xl",

                        src: D.journey.building,
                        alt: "Sandra's SSELFIE editorial example",
                        className: "w-full h-full object-cover transition-transform duration-700 ease-out group-hover:scale-105"
                    })
                }), i.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "space-y-8 w-full lg:w-1/2",
                    children: [i.jsx("h2", {
                        className: "text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-light leading-tight tracking-[-0.01em] text-[#171719]",
                        style: {
                            fontFamily: "Times New Roman, serif",
                            fontWeight: 300
                        },
                        children: "Okay, here's what actually happened..."
                    }), i.jsxs("div", {
                        className: "space-y-6 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-[#171719] font-light font-inter",
                        children: [i.jsx("p", {
                            children: "One year ago my marriage ended. Single mom, three kids, zero plan."
                        }), i.jsx("p", {
                            children: "But I had a phone. And I figured out that was all I needed."
                        }), i.jsx("p", {
                            children: "90 days later: 120K followers. Today: A business that actually works. Now: Teaching you exactly how I did it."
                        }), i.jsx("p", {
                            children: "No fancy equipment. No design degree. Just strategy that actually works."
                        })]
                    })]
                })]
            })
        })
    })
}
const cu = ({isOpen: e, onClose: t, onEmailCaptured: r, plan: a}) => {
    const [s,n] = g.useState("")
      , [o,l] = g.useState(!1)
      , {toast: c} = he()
      , d = async p => {
        if (p.preventDefault(),
        !s || !s.includes("@")) {
            c({
                title: "Email Required",
                description: "Please enter a valid email address",
                variant: "destructive"
            });
            return
        }
        l(!0);
        try {
            if (!(await fetch("/api/email-capture", {
                method: "POST",
                headers: {
                    "Content-Type": "application/json"
                },
                body: JSON.stringify({
                    email: s,
                    plan: a,
                    source: "landing_page"
                })
            })).ok)
                throw new Error("Failed to capture email");
            localStorage.setItem("emailCaptured", "true"),
            localStorage.setItem("capturedEmail", s),
            c({
                title: "Email Captured!",
                description: "Redirecting to authentication...",
                variant: "default"
            }),
            r && r(s),
            t(),
            setTimeout( () => {
                window.location.href = "/api/login"
            }
            , 1e3)
        } catch {
            c({
                title: "Something went wrong",
                description: "Please try again or contact support",
                variant: "destructive"
            })
        } finally {
            l(!1)
        }
    }
    ;
    if (!e)
        return null;
    const u = a === "free";
    return i.jsx("div", {
        className: "fixed inset-0 bg-black bg-opacity-50 flex items-center justify-center z-50 p-4",
        children: i.jsxs("div", {
            className: "bg-white max-w-4xl w-full max-h-[90vh] overflow-y-auto relative",
            children: [i.jsx("button", {
                onClick: t,
                className: "absolute top-4 right-4 text-black hover:text-gray-600 text-2xl font-light z-10",
                children: "×"
            }), i.jsxs("div", {
                className: "flex flex-col lg:flex-row min-h-[500px]",
                children: [i.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "lg:w-1/2 relative min-h-[300px] lg:min-h-[500px]",
                    children: [i.jsx("img", {
                        src: D.emailCapture,
                        alt: "SSELFIE Studio",
                        className: "w-full h-full object-cover"
                    }), i.jsx("div", {
                        className: "absolute inset-0 bg-black bg-opacity-30"
                    })]
                }), i.jsx("div", {
                    className: "lg:w-1/2 p-6 sm:p-8 lg:p-12 flex flex-col justify-center min-h-[400px]",
                    children: i.jsxs("div", {
                        className: "max-w-md mx-auto w-full",
                        children: [i.jsx("div", {
                            className: "text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.4em] text-gray-500 mb-6",
                            children: u ? "Start Free" : "Join SSELFIE Studio"
                        }), i.jsx("h2", {
                            className: "font-serif text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-light text-black mb-4 leading-tight",
                            children: u ? i.jsxs(i.Fragment, {
                                children: ["Your first 5 AI photos", i.jsx("br", {}), "are on me"]
                            }) : i.jsxs(i.Fragment, {
                                children: ["Ready to build", i.jsx("br", {}), "your empire?"]
                            })
                        }), i.jsx("p", {
                            className: "text-gray-600 mb-8 leading-relaxed",
                            children: u ? "Upload your phone selfies, get photos that look like you hired a fancy photographer. No studio required." : "Join 1,000+ women building their personal brands with AI. Get 100 monthly images, Maya & Victoria AI, and everything you need to launch."
                        }), i.jsxs("form", {
                            onSubmit: d,
                            className: "space-y-6",
                            children: [i.jsx("div", {
                                children: i.jsx("input", {
                                    type: "email",
                                    value: s,
                                    onChange: p => n(p.target.value),
                                    placeholder: "Enter your email address",
                                    className: "w-full px-4 py-4 border border-gray-200 focus:border-black focus:outline-none text-sm",
                                    required: !0
                                })
                            }), i.jsx("button", {
                                type: "submit",
                                disabled: o,
                                className: "w-full py-4 bg-black text-white text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] hover:bg-gray-800 transition-all duration-300 disabled:opacity-50",
                                children: o ? "Getting Started..." : u ? "Get My 5 Free Photos" : "Start Studio $47/mo"
                            })]
                        }), i.jsx("p", {
                            className: "text-xs text-gray-500 mt-4 text-center",
                            children: u ? "No credit card required. Start creating immediately." : "30-day money-back guarantee. Cancel anytime."
                        })]
                    })
                })]
            })]
        })
    })
}

const _a = ({backgroundImage: e, tagline: t, title: r, subtitle: a, ctaText: s, ctaLink: n, overlay: o=.4, alignment: l="center", fullHeight: c=!0}) => {
    const d = u => {
        if (n != null && n.startsWith("#")) {
            u.preventDefault();
            const p = document.querySelector(n);
            p == null || p.scrollIntoView({
                behavior: "smooth"
            })
        }
    }
    ;
    return i.jsxs("section", {
        className: `relative w-full ${c ? "h-screen" : "min-h-[600px]"} flex items-center overflow-hidden bg-luxury-black`,
        children: [i.jsxs("div", {

                src: e,
                alt: "",
                className: "w-full h-full object-cover editorial-hover"
            }), i.jsx("div", {

                style: {
                    opacity: o
                }
            })]
        }), i.jsx("div", {
            className: "relative z-10 w-full h-full flex items-center justify-center",
            children: i.jsxs("div", {
                className: `max-w-6xl mx-auto px-8 ${l === "center" ? "text-center" : ""}`,
                children: [t && i.jsx("p", {
                    className: "text-xs tracking-ultra-wide uppercase text-white/60 mb-8 system-font font-light",
                    children: t
                }), i.jsx("h1", {
                    className: "hero-title text-white text-[clamp(4rem,12vw,10rem)] mb-8",
                    children: r
                }), a && i.jsx("p", {
                    className: "text-2xl tracking-ultra-wide uppercase text-white/80 mb-12 system-font font-light",
                    children: a
                }), s && n && i.jsx("a", {
                    href: n,
                    onClick: d,
                    className: "editorial-cta",
                    children: s
                })]
            })
        })]
    })
}

function PN() {
    const {user: e, isAuthenticated: t} = dt()
      , {toast: r} = he()
      , [,a] = ve()
      , [s,n] = g.useState(1)
      , [o,l] = g.useState([])
      , c = g.useRef(null)
      , [d,u] = g.useState({
        brandStory: "",
        personalMission: "",
        businessGoals: "",
        targetAudience: "",
        businessType: "",
        brandVoice: "",
        stylePreferences: "",
        selfieUploadStatus: "pending",
        aiTrainingStatus: "not_started",
        currentStep: 1,
        completed: !1
    })
      , p = 6
      , h = Je({
        mutationFn: async w => pe("POST", "/api/onboarding", w),
        onSuccess: w => {
            console.log("Onboarding data saved successfully:", w)
        }
        ,
        onError: w => {
            console.error("Failed to save onboarding data:", w)
        }
    })
      , f = Je({
        mutationFn: async w => pe("POST", "/api/start-model-training", {
            selfieImages: w
        }),
        onSuccess: () => {
            u(w => ({
                ...w,
                aiTrainingStatus: "in_progress"
            })),
            y()
        }
        ,
        onError: w => {
            r({
                title: "Training failed",
                description: "Failed to start AI training. Please try again.",
                variant: "destructive"
            })
        }
    })
      , y = () => {
        if (s < p) {
            const w = s + 1;
            n(w),
            u(k => ({
                ...k,
                currentStep: w
            })),
            h.mutate({
                ...d,
                currentStep: w
            })
        } else {
            const w = {
                ...d,
                completed: !0,
                currentStep: p
            };
            h.mutate(w),
            a("/workspace")
        }
    }
      , x = () => {
        if (s > 1) {
            const w = s - 1;
            n(w),
            u(k => ({
                ...k,
                currentStep: w
            }))
        }
    }
      , N = (w, k) => {
        u(E => ({
            ...E,
            [w]: k
        }))
    }
      , v = w => {
        const k = Array.from(w.target.files || [])
          , E = k.filter(C => {
            const T = C.type.startsWith("image/")
              , R = C.size <= 10 * 1024 * 1024;
            return T && R
        }
        );
        E.length !== k.length && r({
            title: "Invalid files",
            description: "Please upload only image files under 10MB.",
            variant: "destructive"
        }),
        l(C => [...C, ...E])
    }
      , m = w => {
        l(k => k.filter( (E, C) => C !== w))
    }
      , b = () => {
        if (o.length < 10) {
            r({
                title: "Not enough photos",
                description: "Please upload at least 10 selfies for AI training.",
                variant: "destructive"
            });
            return
        }
        const w = o.map(k => new Promise(E => {
            const C = new FileReader;
            C.onloadend = () => E(C.result),
            C.readAsDataURL(k)
        }
        ));
        Promise.all(w).then(k => {
            f.mutate(k)
        }
        )
    }
      , j = s / p * 100;
    return t ? i.jsxs("div", {

function aa({children: e, requiredPlan: t}) {
    const {user: r, isAuthenticated: a} = dt()
      , {toast: s} = he()
      , [,n] = ve()
      , [o,l] = g.useState(!1)
      , [c,d] = g.useState(!0)
      , {data: u, isLoading: p} = ae({
        queryKey: ["/api/subscription"],
        enabled: a && (r == null ? void 0 : r.email) !== "ssa@ssasocial.com",
        retry: 1,
        staleTime: 5 * 60 * 1e3,
        refetchOnWindowFocus: !1,
        refetchOnMount: !1
    });
    return g.useEffect( () => {
        if (!a) {
            n("/pricing");
            return
        }
        if ((r == null ? void 0 : r.email) === "ssa@ssasocial.com") {
            l(!0),
            d(!1);
            return
        }
        if (p)
            return;
        const h = u && u.status === "active";
        if (t && !((u == null ? void 0 : u.plan) === t)) {
            s({
                title: "Upgrade Required",
                description: `This feature requires ${t} subscription.`,
                variant: "destructive"
            }),
            n("/pricing");
            return
        }
        if (!h) {
            s({
                title: "Payment Required",
                description: "Please complete your payment to access member features.",
                variant: "destructive"
            }),
            n("/pricing");
            return
        }
        l(!0),
        d(!1)
    }
    , [a, u, p, t, r == null ? void 0 : r.email, s, n]),
    !a || c || p ? i.jsx("div", {
        className: "min-h-screen bg-white flex items-center justify-center",
        children: i.jsxs("div", {
            className: "text-center",
            children: [i.jsx("div", {
                className: "animate-spin w-8 h-8 border-4 border-[#0a0a0a] border-t-transparent rounded-full mx-auto mb-4"
            }), i.jsx("p", {
                className: "text-sm text-[#666666]",
                children: "Verifying access..."
            })]
        })
    }) : o ? i.jsx(i.Fragment, {
        children: e
    }) : i.jsx("div", {
        className: "min-h-screen bg-white flex items-center justify-center",
        children: i.jsxs("div", {
            className: "text-center",
            children: [i.jsx("h2", {
                className: "text-2xl font-light mb-4",
                style: {
                    fontFamily: "Times New Roman, serif"
                },
                children: "Access Denied"
            }), i.jsx("p", {
                className: "text-[#666666] mb-8",
                children: "You need a valid subscription to access this feature."
            }), i.jsx("button", {
                onClick: () => n("/pricing"),
                className: "bg-[#0a0a0a] text-white px-8 py-4 text-xs uppercase tracking-wider hover:bg-[#333] transition-colors",
                children: "View Pricing"
            })]
        })
    })
}
function YN() {
    const {user: e, isAuthenticated: t} = dt()
      , {toast: r} = he()
      , a = ct()
      , [s,n] = g.useState(!1)
      , {data: o, isLoading: l} = ae({
        queryKey: ["/api/profile"],
        enabled: t,
        retry: !1
    })
      , c = Je({
        mutationFn: async f => await pe("PUT", "/api/profile", f),
        onSuccess: () => {
            r({
                title: "Profile Updated",
                description: "Your profile has been saved successfully."
            }),
            a.invalidateQueries({
                queryKey: ["/api/profile"]
            }),
            n(!1)
        }
        ,
        onError: f => {
            r({
                title: "Update Failed",
                description: f.message || "Failed to update profile.",
                variant: "destructive"
            })
        }
    })
      , [d,u] = g.useState({
        fullName: (o == null ? void 0 : o.fullName) || "",
        phone: (o == null ? void 0 : o.phone) || "",
        location: (o == null ? void 0 : o.location) || "",
        instagramHandle: (o == null ? void 0 : o.instagramHandle) || "",
        websiteUrl: (o == null ? void 0 : o.websiteUrl) || "",
        bio: (o == null ? void 0 : o.bio) || "",
        brandVibe: (o == null ? void 0 : o.brandVibe) || "",
        goals: (o == null ? void 0 : o.goals) || ""
    });
    ee.useEffect( () => {
        o && u({
            fullName: o.fullName || "",
            phone: o.phone || "",
            location: o.location || "",
            instagramHandle: o.instagramHandle || "",
            websiteUrl: o.websiteUrl || "",
            bio: o.bio || "",
            brandVibe: o.brandVibe || "",
            goals: o.goals || ""
        })
    }
    , [o]);
    const p = f => {
        f.preventDefault(),
        c.mutate(d)
    }
      , h = (f, y) => {
        u(x => ({
            ...x,
            [f]: y
        }))
    }
    ;
    return t ? i.jsx(aa, {
        children: i.jsxs("div", {
            className: "min-h-screen bg-white",

                className: "relative min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center bg-black text-white overflow-hidden",

                    className: "absolute inset-0 opacity-30",
                    children: i.jsx("img", {
                        src: (e == null ? void 0 : e.profileImageUrl) || D.editorial.luxury1,

                            objectPosition: "center top"
                        }
                    })
                }), i.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "relative z-10 text-center max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 flex flex-col justify-end min-h-screen pb-16 sm:pb-20",

                        style: {

                            color: "rgba(255,255,255,0.7)",

                        },
                        children: "Your Personal Brand Foundation"
                    }), i.jsx("h1", {
                        style: {
                            fontSize: "clamp(3rem, 8vw, 8rem)",
                            lineHeight: .9,
                            fontWeight: 200,
                            color: "white",
                            marginBottom: "clamp(16px, 3vw, 24px)",

                            textTransform: "uppercase",
                            maxWidth: "100%",
                            overflowWrap: "break-word"
                        },
                        children: "PROFILE"
                    }), i.jsx("div", {

            icon: "h-10 w-10"

    defaultVariants: {
        variant: "default",
        size: "default"
    }
})

                    }, p))
                })]
            })
        })]
    })
}

function Sm() {
    const {user: e, isAuthenticated: t} = dt()
      , [r,a] = g.useState(null)
      , [s,n] = g.useState(!1)
      , o = ct()
      , {data: l=[], isLoading: c} = ae({
        queryKey: ["/api/gallery-images"],
        enabled: t
    })
      , {data: d} = ae({
        queryKey: ["/api/images/favorites"],
        enabled: t
    })
      , u = (d == null ? void 0 : d.favorites) || []
      , p = Je({
        mutationFn: async m => {
            console.log("Making API request to toggle favorite for image:", m);
            const b = await pe("POST", `/api/images/${m}/favorite`);
            return console.log("Favorite toggle response:", b),
            b
        }
        ,
        onSuccess: m => {
            console.log("Favorite toggle success:", m),
            o.invalidateQueries({
                queryKey: ["/api/images/favorites"]
            })
        }
        ,
        onError: m => {
            console.error("Favorite toggle error:", m)
        }
    })
      , h = Je({
        mutationFn: async m => await pe("DELETE", `/api/ai-images/${m}`),
        onSuccess: () => {
            o.invalidateQueries({
                queryKey: ["/api/gallery-images"]
            }),
            o.invalidateQueries({
                queryKey: ["/api/images/favorites"]
            })
        }
    })
      , f = async (m, b) => {
        try {
            if (!m || !m.startsWith("http")) {
                console.log("Skipping invalid URL:", m);
                return
            }
            const j = await fetch(m);
            if (!j.ok) {
                console.log("Failed to download image:", j.status, m);
                return
            }
            const w = await j.blob()
              , k = window.URL.createObjectURL(w)
              , E = document.createElement("a");
            E.href = k,
            E.download = b,
            document.body.appendChild(E),
            E.click(),
            document.body.removeChild(E),
            window.URL.revokeObjectURL(k)
        } catch (j) {
            console.error("Error downloading image:", j)
        }
    }
      , y = async () => {
        const m = s ? l.filter(b => u.includes(b.id)) : l;
        for (let b = 0; b < m.length; b++) {
            const j = m[b];
            await f(j.imageUrl, `sselfie-${b + 1}.jpg`),
            await new Promise(w => setTimeout(w, 500))
        }
    }
      , x = m => {
        console.log("Heart clicked for image:", m),
        console.log("Current favorites:", u),
        console.log("Is currently favorite:", u.includes(m)),
        p.mutate(m)
    }
      , N = m => {
        confirm("Are you sure you want to delete this photo? This action cannot be undone.") && h.mutate(m)
    }
      , v = s ? l.filter(m => u.includes(m.id)) : l;
    return t ? i.jsx(aa, {
        children: i.jsxs("div", {
            className: "min-h-screen bg-white touch-manipulation",
            style: {
                fontFamily: '-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif',
                fontWeight: 300,
                color: "#0a0a0a"
            },
            children: [i.jsx(ye, {}), i.jsx(Gt, {
                backgroundImage: "https://i.postimg.cc/76vVdbWY/out-0-7.png",
                title: "SSELFIE",
                subtitle: "GALLERY",
                tagline: "Your professional photo library",
                alignment: "center",
                overlay: .4
            }), i.jsx("section", {
                style: {
                    padding: "80px 0 60px 0",
                    background: "#ffffff"
                },
                children: i.jsxs("div", {
                    style: {
                        maxWidth: "1400px",
                        margin: "0 auto",
                        padding: "0 6vw"
                    },
                    children: [i.jsx("div", {
                        style: {
                            textAlign: "center",
                            marginBottom: "60px"
                        },
                        children: i.jsx("p", {
                            style: {
                                fontSize: "20px",
                                lineHeight: 1.5,
                                fontWeight: 300,
                                maxWidth: "700px",
                                margin: "0 auto 40px auto",
                                color: "#666666"
                            },
                            children: "Every photo here is you, just elevated. Download what serves your brand, delete what doesn't. This is your professional arsenal ready for anything."
                        })
                    }), i.jsxs("div", {
                        style: {
                            display: "flex",
                            justifyContent: "center",
                            gap: "80px",
                            alignItems: "center",
                            marginBottom: "60px",
                            flexWrap: "wrap"
                        },
                        children: [i.jsxs("div", {
                            style: {
                                textAlign: "center"
                            },
                            children: [i.jsx("div", {
                                style: {
                                    fontFamily: "Times New Roman, serif",
                                    fontSize: "64px",
                                    fontWeight: 200,
                                    lineHeight: 1,

                                },
                                children: l.length

function Gk() {
    const [e,t] = g.useState(!1)
      , {data: r} = ae({
        queryKey: ["/api/usage/status"],
        refetchInterval: 3e4
    })
      , {data: a} = ae({
        queryKey: ["/api/usage/stats"],
        refetchInterval: 6e4
    });
    if (!r)
        return null;
    const s = () => r.remainingGenerations >= 999999 ? "text-emerald-600" : r.canGenerate ? r.remainingGenerations <= 10 ? "text-yellow-600" : "text-emerald-600" : "text-red-500"
      , n = () => r.monthlyAllowed ? Math.min((r.monthlyUsed || 0) / r.monthlyAllowed * 100, 100) : Math.min(r.totalUsed / r.totalAllowed * 100, 100)
      , o = l => {
        const c = new Date(l)
          , d = new Date
          , u = Math.ceil((c.getTime() - d.getTime()) / (1e3 * 60 * 60 * 24));
        return u <= 0 ? "Resets today" : u === 1 ? "Resets tomorrow" : `Resets in ${u} days`
    }
    ;
    return i.jsxs("div", {
        className: "bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-none",
        children: [i.jsxs("div", {
            className: "p-4 cursor-pointer hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors",
            onClick: () => t(!e),
            children: [i.jsxs("div", {
                className: "flex justify-between items-center",
                children: [i.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "flex items-center gap-3",
                    children: [i.jsx("div", {
                        className: "text-sm font-medium text-gray-900",
                        children: "Usage"
                    }), i.jsx("div", {
                        className: `text-sm font-bold ${s()}`,
                        children: r.remainingGenerations >= 999999 ? "Unlimited" : `${r.remainingGenerations} remaining`
                    })]
                }), i.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "flex items-center gap-3",
                    children: [!r.canGenerate && i.jsx("div", {
                        className: "text-xs text-red-500 font-medium",
                        children: "LIMIT REACHED"
                    }), i.jsx("div", {
                        className: "text-xs text-gray-400",
                        children: e ? "−" : "+"
                    })]
                })]
            }), i.jsx("div", {
                className: "mt-2 w-full bg-gray-200 rounded-none h-1",
                children: i.jsx("div", {
                    className: `h-1 rounded-none transition-all duration-300 ${r.canGenerate ? "bg-emerald-500" : "bg-red-500"}`,
                    style: {
                        width: `${n()}%`
                    }
                })
            })]
        }), e && a && i.jsxs("div", {
            className: "border-t border-gray-200 p-4 space-y-4",
            children: [i.jsxs("div", {
                children: [i.jsx("div", {
                    className: "text-xs text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium mb-2",
                    children: "Current Plan"
                }), i.jsx("div", {
                    className: "text-sm font-medium text-gray-900 mb-1",
                    children: a.plan === "ai-pack" ? "SSELFIE AI Pack" : a.plan === "studio-founding" ? "Studio Founding" : "Studio Standard"
                }), i.jsx("div", {
                    className: "text-xs text-gray-600",
                    children: a.planLimits.description
                })]
            }), i.jsxs("div", {
                className: "grid grid-cols-2 gap-4",
                children: [i.jsxs("div", {
                    children: [i.jsx("div", {
                        className: "text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1",
                        children: "Used"
                    }), i.jsx("div", {
                        className: "text-sm font-medium text-gray-900",
                        children: a.planLimits.resetMonthly ? `${r.monthlyUsed || 0} this month` : `${r.totalUsed} total`
                    })]
                }), i.jsxs("div", {
                    children: [i.jsx("div", {
                        className: "text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1",
                        children: "Allowed"
                    }), i.jsx("div", {
                        className: "text-sm font-medium text-gray-900",
                        children: a.planLimits.resetMonthly ? `${r.monthlyAllowed || 0}/month` : `${r.totalAllowed} total`
                    })]
                })]
            }), a.planLimits.resetMonthly && r.resetDate && i.jsxs("div", {
                children: [i.jsx("div", {
                    className: "text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1",
                    children: "Next Reset"
                }), i.jsx("div", {
                    className: "text-sm font-medium text-gray-900",
                    children: o(r.resetDate)
                })]
            }), !r.canGenerate && r.reason && i.jsxs("div", {
                className: "bg-red-50 border border-red-200 p-3 rounded-none",
                children: [i.jsx("div", {
                    className: "text-sm text-red-800",
                    children: r.reason
                }), a.plan === "ai-pack" && i.jsx("div", {
                    className: "mt-2",
                    children: i.jsx("a", {
                        href: "/pricing",
                        className: "text-sm text-red-600 hover:text-red-700 underline",
                        children: "Upgrade to Studio for monthly generations"
                    })
                })]
            }), i.jsxs("div", {
                className: "pt-2 border-t border-gray-100",
                children: [i.jsx("div", {
                    className: "text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1",
                    children: "Total Cost Incurred"
                }), i.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "text-sm text-gray-600",
                    children: ["$", a.totalCostIncurred.toFixed(4), " USD"]
                }), i.jsx("div", {
                    className: "text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1",
                    children: "Each generation costs ~$0.038 (4 images)"
                })]
            })]
        })]
    })
}
function Wk() {
    const {isAuthenticated: e} = dt()
      , {toast: t} = he()
      , r = ct()
      , [a,s] = g.useState(null)
      , [n,o] = g.useState(null)
      , [l,c] = g.useState("selection");
    g.useState([]);
    const [d,u] = g.useState({})
      , [p,h] = g.useState(!1)
      , [f,y] = g.useState([])
      , [x,N] = g.useState("")
      , [v,m] = g.useState(!1)
      , {data: b} = ae({
        queryKey: ["/api/user-model"],
        enabled: e
    })
      , {data: j=[], refetch: w} = ae({
        queryKey: ["/api/generated-images"],
        enabled: e,
        refetchInterval: 3e3
    })
      , k = j.filter(M => M.imageUrls && M.imageUrls.length > 0)
      , E = [{
        id: "Editorial",
        name: "Editorial",
        description: "Magazine covers and high-fashion photography",
        subcategories: ["Magazine Cover", "Fashion", "Business"],
        preview: D.portraits.professional[0]
    }, {
        id: "Lifestyle",
        name: "Lifestyle",
        description: "Authentic moments and personal brand",
        subcategories: ["Working", "Travel", "Home", "Social"],
        preview: D.portraits.professional[4]
    }, {
        id: "Portrait",
        name: "Portrait",
        description: "Professional headshots and creative portraits",
        subcategories: ["Headshot", "Creative", "Professional"],
        preview: D.portraits.professional[1]
    }, {
        id: "Luxury",
        name: "Luxury",
        description: "Sophisticated luxury lifestyle photography",
        subcategories: ["Yacht", "Villa", "Shopping", "Events"],
        preview: D.portraits.professional[6]
    }]
      , C = Je({
        mutationFn: async M => await (await pe("POST", "/api/generate-user-images", M)).json(),
        onSuccess: M => {
            console.log("Generation response:", M),
            c("processing"),
            t({
                title: "Creating your brand photoshoot!",
                description: `Generating ${a} ${n} images with your personal AI...`
            }),
            M.predictionId ? T(M.generatedImageId, M.predictionId) : (console.error("No prediction ID received:", M),
            t({
                title: "Generation Error",
                description: "No prediction ID received from generation service",
                variant: "destructive"
            }),
            c("selection"))
        }
        ,
        onError: M => {
            M.message.includes("Usage limit reached") || M.message.includes("Generation limit reached") ? (t({
                title: "Usage Limit Reached",
                description: "You've reached your generation limit. Upgrade your plan to continue creating AI images.",
                variant: "destructive"
            }),
            r.invalidateQueries({
                queryKey: ["/api/usage/status"]
            }),
            r.invalidateQueries({
                queryKey: ["/api/usage/stats"]
            })) : t({
                title: "Generation failed",
                description: M.message,
                variant: "destructive"
            }),
            c("selection")
        }
    })
      , T = async (M, A) => {
        if (!A) {
            t({
                title: "Generation Error",
                description: "No prediction ID received from generation service",
                variant: "destructive"
            }),
            c("selection");
            return
        }
        let P = 0;
        const I = 100
          , z = setInterval(async () => {
            P++;
            try {
                const X = (await pe("GET", "/api/generated-images")).find(K => K.id === M);
                if (X && X.generationStatus === "completed" && X.image_urls !== "processing") {
                    clearInterval(z),
                    c("results"),
                    w(),
                    t({
                        title: "Photoshoot Complete!",
                        description: "Your brand images are ready for selection."
                    }),
                    r.invalidateQueries({
                        queryKey: ["/api/usage/status"]
                    }),
                    r.invalidateQueries({
                        queryKey: ["/api/usage/stats"]
                    });
                    return
                }
                if (X && X.generationStatus === "failed") {
                    clearInterval(z),
                    t({
                        title: "Generation Failed",
                        description: "Image generation failed. Please try again with a different style.",
                        variant: "destructive"
                    }),
                    c("selection");
                    return
                }
                try {
                    const K = await pe("GET", `/api/check-generation/${A}`);
                    if (K.status === "succeeded")
                        await pe("POST", `/api/ai/update-status/${M}/${A}`);
                    else if (K.status === "failed") {
                        clearInterval(z),
                        t({
                            title: "Generation Failed",
                            description: K.error || "Image generation failed. Please try again.",
                            variant: "destructive"
                        }),
                        c("selection");
                        return
                    }
                } catch (K) {
                    console.warn("API status check failed, will retry:", K)
                }
            } catch (O) {
                console.error("Polling error:", O),
                P >= I && (clearInterval(z),
                t({
                    title: "Generation in Progress",
                    description: "Your images are still being created. They will appear once ready.",
                    variant: "default"
                }))
            }
            P >= I && (clearInterval(z),
            t({
                title: "Generation Taking Too Long",
                description: "Your images are still being created. Check back in a few minutes!",
                variant: "destructive"
            }),
            c("selection"))
        }
        , 3e3)
    }
      , R = M => {
        s(M),
        o(null)
    }
      , H = M => {
        o(M)
    }
      , _ = () => {
        if (!a || !n) {
            t({
                title: "Please select a style",
                description: "Choose both a category and subcategory for your photoshoot.",
                variant: "destructive"
            });
            return
        }
        if (!b || b.trainingStatus !== "completed") {
            t({
                title: "Model not ready",
                description: "Your personal AI model is still training. Please wait for completion.",
                variant: "destructive"
            });
            return
        }
        C.mutate({
            category: a,
            subcategory: n
        })
    }
      , Y = (M, A) => {
        u(P => ({
            ...P,
            [M]: A
        }))
    }
      , F = () => {
        c("integration")
    }
      , U = g.useCallback(async () => {
        if (!x.trim())
            return;
        const M = x.trim();
        N(""),
        m(!0);
        const A = [...f, {
            role: "user",
            content: M
        }];
        y(A);
        try {
            const P = await pe("POST", "/api/sandra-custom-prompt", {
                message: M,
                context: "brand_photoshoot"
            })
              , I = P.message
              , z = P.generatedPrompt;
            y(O => [...O, {
                role: "sandra",
                content: `${I}

I've created this perfect prompt for your vision: "${z}"

Should I generate this for you right now?`,
                prompt: z
            }]),
            t({
                title: "Sandra created your prompt!",
                description: "Click 'Generate Now' to create your images"
            })
        } catch (P) {
            console.error("Sandra chat error:", P),
            y(I => [...I, {
                role: "sandra",
                content: "Oops! I'm having a moment. Try describing your vision again - I'm listening!"
            }])
        } finally {
            m(!1)
        }
    }
    , [x, f, t])
      , $ = g.useCallback(async M => {
        m(!0);
        try {
            const A = await pe("POST", "/api/generate-custom-prompt", {
                customPrompt: M
            });
            t({
                title: "Generation Started!",
                description: "Your custom images are being created. Check back in a few moments."
            }),
            w(),
            c("processing")
        } catch (A) {
            console.error("Custom generation error:", A),
            t({
                title: "Generation Failed",
                description: "Try again or choose a different style",
                variant: "destructive"
            })
        } finally {
            m(!1)
        }
    }
    , [t, w]);
    return e ? i.jsx(aa, {
        children: i.jsxs("div", {
            className: "min-h-screen bg-white",
            children: [i.jsx(ye, {}), i.jsxs("div", {
                className: "pt-32 pb-16",
                children: [i.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "text-center mb-16 px-8",
                    children: [i.jsx("h1", {
                        className: "text-4xl md:text-6xl font-light mb-6",
                        style: {
                            fontFamily: "Times New Roman, serif"
                        },
                        children: "YOUR BRAND PHOTOSHOOT"
                    }), i.jsxs("p", {
                        className: "text-lg text-[#666] max-w-2xl mx-auto",
                        children: [l === "selection" && "Choose your style and create professional images with your personal AI", l === "processing" && "Your AI is creating magazine-quality images", l === "results" && "Here's your transformation", l === "integration" && "Ready to build your brand?"]
                    })]
                }), i.jsx("div", {
                    className: "max-w-4xl mx-auto px-8 mb-12",
                    children: i.jsx(Gk, {})
                }), i.jsx("div", {
                    className: "flex justify-center mb-16",
                    children: i.jsx("div", {
                        className: "flex items-center space-x-8",
                        children: ["selection", "processing", "results", "integration"].map( (M, A) => i.jsxs("div", {
                            className: "flex items-center",
                            children: [i.jsx("div", {
                                className: `w-8 h-8 rounded-full border-2 flex items-center justify-center text-sm ${l === M || A < ["selection", "processing", "results", "integration"].indexOf(l) ? "border-[#0a0a0a] bg-[#0a0a0a] text-white" : "border-[#ccc] text-[#ccc]"}`,
                                children: String(A + 1).padStart(2, "0")
                            }), A < 3 && i.jsx("div", {
                                className: "w-16 h-px bg-[#e5e5e5] mx-4"
                            })]
                        }, M))
                    })
                }), l === "selection" && i.jsx(Bk, {
                    categories: E,
                    selectedStyle: a,
                    selectedSubcategory: n,
                    onStyleSelect: R,
                    onSubcategorySelect: H,
                    onStartPhotoshoot: _,
                    isLoading: C.isPending,
                    userModel: b
                }), l === "processing" && i.jsx(Uk, {
                    selectedStyle: a,
                    selectedSubcategory: n
                }), l === "results" && i.jsx(Yk, {
                    generatedImages: k,
                    selectedImages: d,
                    onImageSelection: Y,
                    onUseToBrandbook: F
                }), i.jsx(qk, {
                    isOpen: p,
                    onToggle: () => h(!p),
                    messages: f,
                    input: x,
                    onInputChange: N,
                    onSendMessage: U,
                    onGeneratePrompt: $,
                    isGenerating: v
                }), l === "integration" && i.jsx($k, {
                    selectedImages: d
                })]
            })]
        })
    }) : i.jsxs("div", {
        className: "min-h-screen bg-white",
        children: [i.jsx(ye, {}), i.jsx("div", {
            className: "pt-32 pb-16 text-center",
            children: i.jsx("h1", {
                children: "Please log in to access Your Brand Photoshoot"
            })
        })]
    })
}
function Bk({categories: e, selectedStyle: t, selectedSubcategory: r, onStyleSelect: a, onSubcategorySelect: s, onStartPhotoshoot: n, isLoading: o, userModel: l}) {
    var c;
    return i.jsxs("div", {
        className: "max-w-4xl mx-auto px-8",
        children: [l && i.jsxs("div", {
            className: "mb-8 p-4 bg-[#f5f5f5] border border-[#e5e5e5]",
            children: [i.jsxs("p", {
                className: "text-sm text-[#666]",
                children: ["Your personal AI model: ", i.jsx("span", {
                    className: "font-medium text-[#0a0a0a]",
                    children: l.trainingStatus === "completed" ? "Ready" : l.trainingStatus === "training" ? "Training in progress..." : "Not available"
                })]
            }), l.trainingStatus === "training" && i.jsx("p", {
                className: "text-xs text-[#999] mt-1",
                children: "Training typically takes 24-48 hours. You'll be notified when ready."
            })]
        }), i.jsxs("div", {
            className: "mb-12",
            children: [i.jsx("h3", {
                className: "text-xl font-light mb-8",
                style: {
                    fontFamily: "Times New Roman, serif"
                },
                children: "01. Choose your photoshoot style"
            }), i.jsx("div", {
                className: "grid grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6",
                children: e.map(d => i.jsxs("button", {
                    onClick: () => a(d.id),
                    className: `p-6 border text-left transition-all ${t === d.id ? "border-[#0a0a0a] bg-[#0a0a0a] text-white" : "border-[#e5e5e5] hover:border-[#0a0a0a]"}`,
                    children: [i.jsx("img", {
                        src: d.preview,
                        alt: d.name,
                        className: "w-full h-32 object-cover mb-4"
                    }), i.jsx("h4", {
                        className: "font-medium mb-2",
                        children: d.name
                    }), i.jsx("p", {
                        className: "text-xs opacity-80",
                        children: d.description
                    })]
                }, d.id))
            })]
        }), t && i.jsxs("div", {
            className: "mb-12",
            children: [i.jsx("h3", {
                className: "text-xl font-light mb-8",
                style: {
                    fontFamily: "Times New Roman, serif"
                },
                children: "02. Select specific style"
            }), i.jsx("div", {
                className: "grid grid-cols-3 gap-4",
                children: (c = e.find(d => d.id === t)) == null ? void 0 : c.subcategories.map(d => i.jsx("button", {
                    onClick: () => s(d),
                    className: `p-4 border text-center transition-all ${r === d ? "border-[#0a0a0a] bg-[#0a0a0a] text-white" : "border-[#e5e5e5] hover:border-[#0a0a0a]"}`,
                    children: d
                }, d))
            })]
        }), t && r && i.jsx("div", {
            className: "text-center",
            children: i.jsx("button", {
                onClick: n,
                disabled: o || (l == null ? void 0 : l.trainingStatus) !== "completed",
                className: "text-[#0a0a0a] border-b border-[#0a0a0a] pb-1 text-lg tracking-wide hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity disabled:opacity-50",
                children: o ? "Starting Your Photoshoot..." : "Start Your Brand Photoshoot"
            })
        })]
    })
}

            })]
        })]

}
function Yk({generatedImages: e, selectedImages: t, onImageSelection: r, onUseToBrandbook: a}) {
    const {toast: s} = he()
      , n = ct()
      , [o,l] = g.useState(new Set)
      , [c,d] = g.useState(new Set)
      , u = e.filter(f => f.generationStatus === "completed" && f.image_urls && f.image_urls !== "processing").slice(-1)[0];
    let p = [];
    if (u && u.image_urls)
        try {
            p = JSON.parse(u.image_urls)
        } catch (f) {
            console.error("Failed to parse image URLs:", f),
            p = []
        }
    const h = async (f, y) => {
        if (!(o.has(f) || c.has(f))) {
            d(x => new Set([...x, f]));
            try {
                await pe("POST", "/api/save-to-gallery", {
                    imageUrl: f,
                    prompt: `${u.category} ${u.subcategory} - Option ${y + 1}`,
                    style: u.category,
                    subcategory: u.subcategory
                }),
                l(x => new Set([...x, f])),
                n.invalidateQueries({
                    queryKey: ["/api/gallery-images"]
                }),
                s({
                    title: "Saved to Gallery",
                    description: "Image permanently saved to your gallery with S3 storage"
                })
            } catch (x) {
                console.error("Error saving to gallery:", x),
                s({
                    title: "Save Failed",
                    description: "Could not save image to gallery. Please try again.",
                    variant: "destructive"
                })
            } finally {
                d(x => {
                    const N = new Set(x);
                    return N.delete(f),
                    N
                }
                )
            }
        }
    }
    ;
    return i.jsxs("div", {
        className: "max-w-4xl mx-auto px-8",
        children: [i.jsxs("div", {
            className: "mb-8 p-6 bg-[#f5f5f5] border border-[#e5e5e5]",
            children: [i.jsx("h4", {
                className: "font-medium mb-3 text-[#0a0a0a]",
                children: "About Your SSELFIE AI"
            }), i.jsx("p", {
                className: "text-sm text-[#666] mb-2",
                children: "AI sometimes gets it wrong and photos may not look exactly like you. This is completely normal! The more you use your SSELFIE AI, the better it gets at learning your exact features."
            }), i.jsx("p", {
                className: "text-sm text-[#666]",
                children: "Choose the best images from each generation and keep creating more. Each photoshoot helps train your AI to be more accurate."
            })]
        }), i.jsxs("div", {
            className: "mb-12",
            children: [i.jsx("h3", {
                className: "text-2xl font-light mb-8 text-center",
                style: {
                    fontFamily: "Times New Roman, serif"
                },
                children: "Your Brand Photoshoot Results"
            }), p.length > 0 ? i.jsxs(i.Fragment, {
                children: [i.jsx("div", {
                    className: "grid grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8",
                    children: p.map( (f, y) => i.jsxs("div", {
                        className: "group relative",
                        children: [i.jsxs("div", {
                            className: "relative mb-4",
                            children: [i.jsx("img", {
                                src: f,
                                alt: `Generated ${u.category} ${u.subcategory} option ${y + 1}`,
                                className: "w-full h-64 object-cover border border-[#e5e5e5]",
                                onError: x => {
                                    x.target.src = D.aiGallery[y % D.aiGallery.length]
                                }
                            }), i.jsx("button", {
                                onClick: () => h(f, y),
                                disabled: c.has(f),
                                style: {
                                    position: "absolute",
                                    top: "16px",
                                    right: "16px",
                                    background: o.has(f) ? "rgba(255, 68, 68, 0.9)" : "rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6)",
                                    border: "none",
                                    color: "#ffffff",
                                    fontSize: "20px",
                                    padding: "8px 10px",
                                    cursor: c.has(f) ? "not-allowed" : "pointer",
                                    borderRadius: "50%",
                                    transition: "all 300ms ease",
                                    backdropFilter: "blur(10px)",
                                    zIndex: 10
                                },
                                onMouseEnter: x => {
                                    c.has(f) || (x.currentTarget.style.background = o.has(f) ? "rgba(255, 68, 68, 1)" : "rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8)",
                                    x.currentTarget.style.transform = "scale(1.1)")
                                }
                                ,
                                onMouseLeave: x => {
                                    c.has(f) || (x.currentTarget.style.background = o.has(f) ? "rgba(255, 68, 68, 0.9)" : "rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6)",
                                    x.currentTarget.style.transform = "scale(1)")
                                }
                                ,
                                children: c.has(f) ? "⟳" : o.has(f) ? "♥" : "♡"
                            }), o.has(f) && i.jsx("div", {
                                style: {
                                    position: "absolute",
                                    bottom: "16px",
                                    left: "16px",
                                    background: "rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.9)",
                                    color: "#ffffff",
                                    fontSize: "10px",
                                    padding: "4px 8px",
                                    borderRadius: "12px",
                                    fontWeight: 500,
                                    letterSpacing: "0.1em",
                                    textTransform: "uppercase",
                                    backdropFilter: "blur(10px)",
                                    zIndex: 5
                                },
                                children: "Saved to Gallery"
                            })]
                        }), i.jsxs("p", {
                            className: "text-sm text-[#666] text-center",
                            children: ["Option ", y + 1, " • ", u.category, " ", u.subcategory]
                        })]
                    }, y))
                }), i.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "text-center space-y-4",
                    children: [i.jsxs("div", {
                        className: "flex gap-4 justify-center",
                        children: [i.jsx("button", {
                            onClick: () => window.location.reload(),
                            className: "text-[#0a0a0a] border border-[#0a0a0a] px-8 py-3 hover:bg-[#0a0a0a] hover:text-white transition-all",
                            children: "Generate More Images"
                        }), o.size > 0 && i.jsxs("a", {
                            href: "/sselfie-gallery",
                            className: "inline-block text-white bg-[#0a0a0a] px-8 py-3 hover:opacity-80 transition-opacity",
                            children: ["View Gallery (", o.size, " saved)"]
                        })]
                    }), i.jsx("p", {
                        className: "text-sm text-[#666] max-w-lg mx-auto",
                        children: "Click the heart (♡) on your favorite images to save them permanently to your gallery. Only saved images will appear in your gallery collection."
                    })]
                })]
            }) : i.jsxs("div", {
                className: "text-center py-16",
                children: [i.jsx("div", {
                    className: "mb-4",
                    children: i.jsx("div", {
                        className: "inline-block w-8 h-8 border-4 border-[#e5e5e5] border-t-[#0a0a0a] rounded-full animate-spin"
                    })
                }), i.jsx("p", {
                    className: "text-[#666] mb-2",
                    children: "Your images are still being created..."
                }), i.jsx("p", {
                    className: "text-sm text-[#999]",
                    children: "This usually takes 2-3 minutes. Please wait."
                })]
            })]
        })]
    })
}

function qk({isOpen: e, onToggle: t, messages: r, input: a, onInputChange: s, onSendMessage: n, onGeneratePrompt: o, isGenerating: l}) {
    return i.jsxs(i.Fragment, {
        children: [i.jsx("div", {
            className: "fixed bottom-8 right-8 z-50",
            children: i.jsx("button", {
                onClick: t,
                className: "bg-[#0a0a0a] text-white p-4 rounded-full shadow-lg hover:bg-[#333] transition-colors",
                children: i.jsx("div", {
                    className: "w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-light",
                    children: e ? "×" : "AI"
                })
            })
        }), e && i.jsxs("div", {
            className: "fixed bottom-24 right-8 w-96 h-[500px] bg-white border border-[#e5e5e5] shadow-xl z-40 flex flex-col",
            children: [i.jsxs("div", {
                className: "p-4 border-b border-[#e5e5e5] bg-[#f5f5f5]",
                children: [i.jsx("h3", {
                    className: "text-lg font-light",
                    style: {
                        fontFamily: "Times New Roman, serif"
                    },
                    children: "Sandra AI Helper"
                }), i.jsx("p", {
                    className: "text-sm text-[#666] mt-1",
                    children: "Tell me what you want to create and I'll generate the perfect prompt"
                })]
            }), i.jsxs("div", {
                className: "flex-1 overflow-y-auto p-4 space-y-4",
                children: [r.length === 0 && i.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "text-center text-[#666] py-8",
                    children: [i.jsx("p", {
                        className: "mb-2",
                        children: "Hey! I'm Sandra 👋"
                    }), i.jsx("p", {
                        className: "text-sm",
                        children: "Describe your vision and I'll create the perfect prompt for your photoshoot"
                    })]
                }), r.map( (c, d) => i.jsx("div", {
                    className: `${c.role === "user" ? "text-right" : "text-left"}`,
                    children: i.jsxs("div", {
                        className: `inline-block max-w-[80%] p-3 rounded ${c.role === "user" ? "bg-[#0a0a0a] text-white" : "bg-[#f5f5f5] text-[#0a0a0a]"}`,
                        children: [i.jsx("p", {
                            className: "text-sm whitespace-pre-wrap",
                            children: c.content
                        }), c.prompt && i.jsx("button", {
                            onClick: () => o(c.prompt),
                            className: "mt-2 text-xs underline hover:no-underline",
                            disabled: l,
                            children: l ? "Generating..." : "Generate Now →"
                        })]
                    })
                }, d))]
            }), i.jsx("div", {
                className: "p-4 border-t border-[#e5e5e5]",
                children: i.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "flex space-x-2",
                    children: [i.jsx("input", {
                        type: "text",
                        value: a,
                        onChange: c => s(c.target.value),
                        onKeyPress: c => c.key === "Enter" && n(),
                        placeholder: "Describe your vision...",
                        className: "flex-1 p-2 border border-[#e5e5e5] text-sm",
                        disabled: l
                    }), i.jsx("button", {
                        onClick: n,
                        disabled: l || !a.trim(),
                        className: "px-4 py-2 bg-[#0a0a0a] text-white text-sm disabled:opacity-50 hover:bg-[#333] transition-colors",
                        children: l ? "..." : "Send"
                    })]
                })
            })]
        })]
    })
}

function Em() {
    const {isAuthenticated: e} = ki()
      , {toast: t} = he()
      , [r,a] = g.useState([])
      , [s,n] = g.useState(!1)
      , [o,l] = g.useState(0)
      , [c,d] = g.useState(null)
      , [u,p] = g.useState("")
      , [h,f] = g.useState(!1)
      , y = g.useRef(null)
      , {data: x, refetch: N} = ae({
        queryKey: ["/api/user-model"],
        retry: !1,
        enabled: !0
    });
    g.useEffect( () => {
        if (s || x && x.trainingStatus === "training") {
            const k = setInterval(async () => {
                if (N(),
                x != null && x.userId)
                    try {
                        const E = await fetch(`/api/training-progress/${x.userId}`);
                        if (E.ok) {
                            const C = await E.json();
                            l(C.progress)
                        }
                    } catch (E) {
                        console.error("Failed to fetch training progress:", E)
                    }
            }
            , 5e3);
            return () => clearInterval(k)
        }
    }
    , [s, x, N]),
    g.useEffect( () => {
        if (c && o > 0) {
            const k = Date.now() - c.getTime()
              , E = 20 * 60 * 1e3
              , C = Math.max(0, E - k)
              , T = Math.floor(C / 6e4)
              , R = Math.floor(C % 6e4 / 1e3);
            p(`${T}:${R.toString().padStart(2, "0")}`)
        }
    }
    , [o, c]);
    const v = Je({
        mutationFn: async k => (await pe("POST", "/api/start-model-training", {
            selfieImages: k
        })).json(),
        onSuccess: () => {
            n(!0),
            d(new Date),
            l(5),
            t({
                title: "Training Started!",
                description: "Your AI model is now training. This takes about 20 minutes."
            })
        }
        ,
        onError: k => {
            console.error("Training failed:", k),
            t({
                title: "Training Failed",
                description: "Images too large or network error. Please try again.",
                variant: "destructive"
            })
        }
    })
      , m = k => {
        const C = Array.from(k.target.files || []).filter(T => {

              , H = T.size <= 10 * 1024 * 1024;

        }

          , T = C.getContext("2d")
          , R = new Image;
        R.onload = () => {
            let {width: Y, height: F} = R;
            Y > F ? Y > 800 && (F = F * 800 / Y,
            Y = 800) : F > 800 && (Y = Y * 800 / F,
            F = 800),
            C.width = Y,
            C.height = F,
            T == null || T.drawImage(R, 0, 0, Y, F);
            const U = C.toDataURL("image/jpeg", .7);

        }
        ,

    }
    )
      , w = async () => {
        if (r.length < 5) {

            });

        }

            title: "Compressing Images",

        });

    }

function Kk() {
    const {user: e, isAuthenticated: t, isLoading: r} = dt()
      , a = () => {
        window.location.href = "/api/login"
    }
      , s = async () => {
        try {
            await fetch("/api/clear-session", {
                method: "POST"
            }),
            window.location.reload()
        } catch (n) {
            console.error("Clear session failed:", n)
        }
    }
    ;
    return i.jsx("div", {
        className: "min-h-screen bg-white flex items-center justify-center",
        children: i.jsxs("div", {
            className: "max-w-md w-full p-8 text-center",
            children: [i.jsx("h1", {
                className: "text-2xl font-light mb-8",
                style: {
                    fontFamily: "Times New Roman, serif"
                },
                children: "Authentication Test"
            }), i.jsx("div", {
                className: "space-y-4 mb-8",
                children: i.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "p-4 border rounded-lg text-left",
                    children: [i.jsx("h3", {
                        className: "font-medium mb-2",
                        children: "Authentication Status"
                    }), i.jsxs("p", {
                        children: [i.jsx("strong", {
                            children: "Loading:"
                        }), " ", r.toString()]
                    }), i.jsxs("p", {
                        children: [i.jsx("strong", {
                            children: "Authenticated:"
                        }), " ", t.toString()]
                    }), i.jsxs("p", {
                        children: [i.jsx("strong", {
                            children: "User ID:"
                        }), " ", (e == null ? void 0 : e.id) || "None"]
                    }), i.jsxs("p", {
                        children: [i.jsx("strong", {
                            children: "Email:"
                        }), " ", (e == null ? void 0 : e.email) || "None"]
                    })]
                })
            }), i.jsxs("div", {
                className: "space-y-4",
                children: [!t && i.jsx("button", {
                    onClick: a,
                    className: "w-full bg-black text-white py-2 px-4 hover:bg-gray-800",
                    children: "Login as Test User"
                }), t && i.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "space-y-4",
                    children: [i.jsx(G, {
                        href: "/workspace",
                        children: i.jsx("button", {
                            className: "w-full bg-black text-white py-2 px-4 hover:bg-gray-800",
                            children: "Go to Workspace"
                        })
                    }), i.jsx("button", {
                        onClick: s,
                        className: "w-full bg-gray-300 text-black py-2 px-4 hover:bg-gray-400",
                        children: "Clear Session"
                    })]
                }), i.jsx(G, {
                    href: "/",
                    children: i.jsx("button", {
                        className: "w-full border border-black py-2 px-4 hover:bg-gray-100",
                        children: "Back to Home"
                    })
                })]
            })]
        })
    })
}

function aS() {
    const {isAuthenticated: e} = ki()
      , {toast: t} = he()
      , r = ct()
      , [a,s] = g.useState(null);
    g.useState(!1);
    const [n,o] = g.useState(!1)
      , [l,c] = g.useState(0)
      , [d,u] = g.useState([])
      , [p,h] = g.useState(null)
      , {data: f} = ae({
        queryKey: ["/api/user-model"],
        enabled: e
    })
      , y = g.useCallback(async m => {
        try {
            if (!(await fetch("/api/save-selected-images", {
                method: "POST",
                headers: {
                    "Content-Type": "application/json"
                },
                body: JSON.stringify({
                    imageUrls: [m],
                    prompt: "Custom Library Image"
                })
            })).ok)
                throw new Error("Failed to save image");
            r.invalidateQueries({
                queryKey: ["/api/gallery-images"]
            }),
            t({
                title: "Image Saved",
                description: "Image added to your gallery"
            })
        } catch (b) {
            console.error("Error saving image:", b),
            t({
                title: "Save Failed",
                description: "Could not save image to gallery",
                variant: "destructive"
            })
        }
    }
    , [r, t])
